    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "WHY DELIVEROO FOR WORK\n\nDeliveroo for Work is growing fast in Belgium, and we’re looking for a Business Development Associate to help shape the future of workplace food.\n\nIn this role, you’ll engage with companies and help them transform how their teams eat at work — from daily employee meals to team lunches, evening shifts and corporate events.\n\nYou’ll work closely with HR, Workplace and Procurement teams to position Deliveroo as their go-to solution for workplace food, while driving new business across the Belgian market.\n\nIf you enjoy building pipelines, opening new opportunities and closing deals in a fast-paced environment, this role offers the chance to make a real commercial impact.\n\nGet to know better our team https://work.deliveroo.be/!\n\nThe role\n\nWe are a small, high-impact team, moving fast, valuing ownership and constantly looking for new ideas.\n\nThis position is based in Brussels with a hybrid working model and will report to the Sales Lead (based in Paris).\n\nThe primary role of the Business Development Associate is to drive new business by engaging with corporations and positioning Deliveroo for Work as their preferred partner for workplace food solutions.\n\nYou will own the full sales cycle, with a strong focus on outbound prospecting, from identifying opportunities to closing deals, while working closely with internal teams to ensure a seamless client experience.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n - Drive new business acquisition across target sectors in Belgium\n\n - Own and manage the full sales cycle from prospecting to closing to activation.\n\n - Proactively build and manage a strong outbound pipeline (cold outreach, LinkedIn, events, referrals)\n\n - Identify new opportunities and use cases (evening meals, group orders, events, gifting, etc.)\n\n - Develop tailored pitches and value propositions based on client needs\n\n - Collaborate closely with Account Management and Customer Service teams to ensure a high-quality client experience\n\n - Contribute to improving sales processes, tools, and go-to-market strategy\n\n - Track performance and maintain a clean, up-to-date pipeline in CRM\n\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\n - Strong commercial mindset with a proactive, ownership-driven attitude\n\n - Experience in B2B sales (outbound experience is a strong plus)\n\n - Comfortable managing a full sales cycle independently\n\n - Excellent organisational skills with the ability to prioritise effectively in a fast-paced environment\n\n - Ability to manage multiple opportunities simultaneously while maintaining a structured and up-to-date pipeline\n\n - Strong communication and negotiation skills\n\n - Analytical mindset with attention to detail\n\n - Resilient and solution-oriented\n\nLanguages:\n\n - French and English are mandatory\n\n - Dutch is a strong plus\n\n\nBENEFITS\n\n - Be part of a fast-growing and impactful business within Deliveroo\n\n - Work in a dynamic, entrepreneurial environment\n\n - Market-competitive salary\n\n - MacBook and phone allowance\n\n - Health insurance (DKV Hospitalisation), meal vouchers\n\n - Company car / car allowance + fuel card\n\n - Contribution to sports activities\n\n - And of course… lots of great food!\n\nWe believe a great workplace reflects the diversity of the world around us. We welcome people of all backgrounds — all you need is a passion for food and a desire to build something meaningful.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
